\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces IGL pipeline as a two-stage algorithm (reproduced from~\cite  {igl2024}). \textbf  {Stage~1} (coordinate discovery): encoder $\Psi $ maps data from the manifold $\mathcal  {M} \subset \mathbb  {R}^D$ to intrinsic coordinates $\xi \in \mathbb  {R}^d$ where the tensor source $\hat  {f}(\zeta )=\DOTSB \sum@ \slimits@ _r w_r\DOTSB \prod@ \slimits@ _j \phi _{r,j}(\zeta ^j)$ decomposes. Green's convolution $G*\hat  {f}$ yields the solution $u(\xi )$. \textbf  {Stage~2} (source fitting): source weights $w_r$ are solved via least squares ($\Phi \mathbf  {w}=\mathbf  {y}$).}}{5}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:igl_pipeline}{{1}{5}{IGL pipeline as a two-stage algorithm (reproduced from~\cite {igl2024}). \textbf {Stage~1} (coordinate discovery): encoder $\Psi $ maps data from the manifold $\mathcal {M} \subset \mathbb {R}^D$ to intrinsic coordinates $\xi \in \mathbb {R}^d$ where the tensor source $\hat {f}(\zeta )=\sum _r w_r\prod _j \phi _{r,j}(\zeta ^j)$ decomposes. Green's convolution $G*\hat {f}$ yields the solution $u(\xi )$. \textbf {Stage~2} (source fitting): source weights $w_r$ are solved via least squares ($\Phi \mathbf {w}=\mathbf {y}$)}{figure.1}{}}
